messages.messageBody:
This goes out to those taking the trip to NYC
which was posted Fri. 14th...
The weather here is cold and damp..just had alittle
snow, which makes the city mucky..
anyhow...it would be cheapest for you to stay
in NJ and take the train/bus in to explore..
look up /digitalcity.com then click onto northern
NJ..we are just a hop, skip, and a jump to the big
apple...Any of the hotels in Secaucus will get you
to the city by bus..try to find a place in Hoboken
NJ..then you can take the ferry over...
best of luck...hope the weather gets just alittle
more friendly for you...anyway....it should be exciting
no matter what...
have a safe trip,
Eileen
